id: pm-ghf1
title: Reserved item-field name collisions are invisible to SDK lint/preflight/harness
description: "An extension can register an item field named like a reserved front-matter key (e.g. 'severity'; FRONT_MATTER_KEY_ORDER) and pass assertExtensionPreflight + createExtensionTestHarness green, but pm create/update rejects the field at runtime — a green package can brick create. Fix: export RESERVED_ITEM_FIELD_NAMES from the SDK and validate registered item-field keys in lintExtensionBlueprint/preflightExtension/harness. Found in 2026-07-02 review (Lane B, pm-6vy7)."
