close_reason: Final bot security finding resolved with immutable public denylist facade and full API tests.
body: "## Context\nFound in the 2026-07-02 ecosystem review (Lane B). An extension can register an item field whose name collides with a reserved front-matter key (e.g. 'severity', 'blocked_reason' — see FRONT_MATTER_KEY_ORDER) and still pass assertExtensionPreflight and createExtensionTestHarness green — but pm create/update rejects the field at runtime. A green package can brick create for its users.\n\n## Approach\nExport RESERVED_ITEM_FIELD_NAMES from the SDK (single source shared with the runtime validator) and validate registered item-field keys in lintExtensionBlueprint, preflightExtension, AND the test harness so the collision fails at authoring time with a rename hint. Known reserved names already bitten in the wild: severity (PR#150), blocked_reason (PR#367).\n\n## Definition of done\nA blueprint registering a reserved field name fails lint/preflight/harness with the same error code; SDK docs list the reserved names; runtime and SDK share one constant (no drift)."
